  "text": "The TLS configuration across the Prometheus monitoring stack is enforced through a centralized TLSConfig struct defined in the prometheus-common library (config/http_config.go), which provides the canonical NewTLSConfig factory function and the HTTPClientConfig wrapper that embeds it.\n\n## TLS Struct Definition and Factory\nThe TLSConfig struct in prometheus-common/config/http_config.go (line 327-339) defines the core TLS configuration fields: CAFile (CA certificate path), CertFile and KeyFile (client certificate/key pairs), ServerName (for SNI), and InsecureSkipVerify. The NewTLSConfig function (line 292-325) creates tls.Config instances by loading certificates from files, validating cert/key pairs, and configuring the TLS client appropriately.\n\n## Config Embedding and Wiring\nThe TLS configuration is embedded into Prometheus's own config structures via HTTPClientConfig. In config/config.go:\n- ScrapeConfig (line 728) embeds HTTPClientConfig for scrape target connections\n- RemoteWriteConfig (line 1212) embeds HTTPClientConfig for remote write endpoints\n- RemoteReadConfig (line 1365) embeds HTTPClientConfig for remote read endpoints\n- TracingConfig (line 925) directly embeds TLSConfig for tracing exporters\n\n## Server-Side TLS (Web Server)\nThe web/web.go file implements server-side TLS through the ServeMultiple function (line 709), which uses the prometheus/exporter-toolkit/web.ServeMultiple to handle TLS configuration from a web config file, enabling HTTPS on the Prometheus web server.\n\n## Client-Side TLS (Outbound Connections)\nTLS is applied to outbound connections through multiple paths:\n\n1. **Scrape targets**: The scrape/scrape.go file creates HTTP clients using config_util.NewClientFromConfig (line 302, 145), which applies the ScrapeConfig.HTTPClientConfig.TLSConfig when scraping metrics from monitored targets.\n\n2. **Remote write**: The storage/remote/write.go and storage/remote/client.go files create remote write clients that apply TLSConfig via NewWriteClient (line 183), which calls config_util.NewClientFromConfig with the HTTPClientConfig.\n\n3. **Remote read**: The storage/remote/read.go and storage/remote/storage.go files create remote read clients similarly using NewReadClient (line 157-159), applying TLSConfig for queries to remote storage.\n\n4. **Tracing exporters**: The tracing/tracing.go file applies TLSConfig directly from TracingConfig (line 189, 222) when creating TLS connections to tracing endpoints via config_util.NewTLSConfig.\n\n## Service Discovery Plugins\nAll service discovery plugins that require network access embed HTTPClientConfig to ensure TLS is available:\n- Kubernetes (kubernetes/kubernetes.go, line 112)\n- Consul (consul/consul.go, line 123)\n- Eureka (eureka/eureka.go, line 75)\n- Marathon (marathon/marathon.go, embedded via HTTPClientConfig)\n- HTTP SD (http/http.go, line 57)\n- XDS (xds/xds.go, line 52)\n- AWS EC2 and Lightsail (aws/ec2.go line 100, aws/lightsail.go line 82)\n- Azure (azure/azure.go, line 118)\n- Hetzner (hetzner/hetzner.go, line 57)\n- IONOS (ionos/ionos.go, line 83)\n- Linode (linode/linode.go, line 88)\n- PuppetDB (puppetdb/puppetdb.go, line 76)\n- Nomad (nomad/nomad.go, line 69)\n- Triton (triton/triton.go)\n- OpenStack (openstack/openstack.go)\n- Vultr, DigitalOcean, and Moby Docker (vultr/vultr.go, digitalocean/digitalocean.go, moby/docker.go, moby/dockerswarm.go)\n\n## TLS Validation (promtool)\nThe cmd/promtool/main.go file implements configuration validation through the CheckConfig function (line 571) and checkTLSConfig helper (line 760-767), which validates that TLS client certificates and keys are properly paired, ensuring configuration correctness before deployment."
